riendship through the lens of severe autism. In a world where public perception of autism is largely shaped by the "quirky geniuses" featured on television shows like The Big Bang Theory and The Good Doctor, We Walk demands that we center our debates about this disorder on those who are most affected by its impacts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAutismxSocial aspects. 0aAutistic peoplexFamily relationships. 0aParents of autistic children. 4aDisability Studies. 4aMemoir. 7aFAMILY & RELATIONSHIPS / Autism Spectrum Disorders.2bisacsh  aautism, intellectual disability, developmental disability, inclusion, medical marijuana, Judaism, ABA.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069046008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501751417?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501751417423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501751417/original  a978-3-11-069046-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020